## <a id='om'></a>Ops Manager Highlights

Ops Manager v1.11 includes the following major features:

### <a id='credhub'></a>CredHub Integration 
Introducing CredHub! CredHub centralizes and secures credential generation, storage, lifecycle management, and access. Debuting in Ops Manager v1.11, CredHub simplifies and improves credential management in PCF. This initial release removes credentials from BOSH deployment manifests. For more information on CredHub integration with PCF, see the [CredHub](../credhub/index.html) topics.

### <a id='nsx'></a>NSX Security Group Integration  

Operators can now configure Ops Manager v1.11 to communicate with VMware NSX. Ops Manager 1.11 supports NSX-V 6.2+. 

This integration makes it easier for operators to define granular firewall access to VMs and apply company networking policies to cloud-native apps. You can use Ops Manager API endpoints to manage the NSX security groups for all your PCF VMs. See [vCenter Config Page](../customizing/vsphere-config.html#vcenter-config) fore more information about the new **NSX Networking** fields in Ops Manager. 

### <a id='azure'></a>Support for Azure Managed Disks 
PCF v1.11 supports [Azure Managed Disks](https://azure.microsoft.com/en-us/services/managed-disks/) for PCF deployments on Azure.

### <a id='opsman'></a>Other Features

For information on other new features in Ops Manager v1.11, see the [Pivotal Cloud Foundry Ops Manager v1.11 Release Notes](../pcf-release-notes/opsmanager-rn.html).

## <a id='ert'></a>Elastic Runtime Highlights

Elastic Runtime v1.11 includes the following major features:

### <a id='container-networking'></a>Container Networking  
No longer a beta feature, Container Networking is now generally available in ERT v1.11. This means that apps running on PCF can now directly communicate with each other, which greatly simplifies the task of creating networking policies. For more information, see the [Administering Container-to-Container Networking](../devguide/deploy-apps/cf-networking.html) topic.

### <a id='nfs3'></a>NFS v3 Volume Services
No longer a beta feature, NFS v3 Volume Services is now generally available in ERT v1.11. Additionally, Elastic Runtime ships with an NFS Volume Service Broker. For more information, see the [Using an External File System (Volume Services)](../devguide/services/using-vol-services.html) and [Enabling NFS Volume Services](../opsguide/enable-vol-services.html) topics.

### <a id='private-doceker'></a>Private Docker Repositories 
With Elastic Runtime v1.11, developers can now push Docker images from private registries that require authentication. For more information, see the [Push a Docker Image with Authentication](../opsguide/docker-registry.html#docker-auth) section of the <em>Using Docker Registries</em> topic.

### <a id='ert'></a>Other Features
For more information on other new features in Elastic Runtime v1.11, see the [Pivotal Elastic Runtime v1.11 Release Notes](../pcf-release-notes/runtime-rn.html).

## <a id='apps-man'></a>Apps Manager Highlights

Apps Manager v1.11 includes the following features:

### <a id='spring-actuator'></a>Spring Actuator 
Apps Manager v1.11 includes Spring Actuator heap dumps, request traces, and thread dumps. For more information, see the [Using Spring Boot Actuators with Apps Manager](../console/using-actuators.html)

### <a id='app-search'></a>App Search 
You can now search for apps across all orgs and spaces by entering the name of the app in the search bar.

### <a id='route-services'></a>Route Services 
You can now manage route services from Apps Manager. For more information, see the [Manage Route Services](../console/manage-apps.html#manage-route-services) section of the <em>Managing Apps and Service Instances Using Apps Manager</em> topic.

### <a id='custom-health-checks'></a>Custom Health Checks 
You can now view custom application health checks in Apps Manager. For more information, see the [View Health Checks](../console/manage-apps.html#health-checks) section of the <em>Managing Apps and Service Instances Using Apps Manager</em> topic.

### <a id='tasks'></a>Tasks in the Usage Report 
The Usage Report now includes information about task usage. For more information, see the [View the Usage Report](../opsguide/accounting-report-apps-man.html#usage-report) section of the <em>Monitoring Instance Usage with Apps Manager</em> topic.

### <a id='last-login'></a>Last Login Notice 
Apps Manager v1.11 displays the date and time of the last login in the bottom right of the footer.

### <a id='section-508a'></a>Section 508a Compliance 
Apps Manager has improved its compliance with [Section 508](https://www.section508.gov/) of the Rehabilitation Act. Customers can now receive an approved Voluntary Product Accessibility Template (VPAT) for Apps Manager.

For more information, see the [Pivotal Elastic Runtime v1.11 Release Notes](../pcf-release-notes/runtime-rn.html).

